<br>
There certainly are ways to fix the cleric epic quest and eliminate most of the problems.  Hopefully someday Verant will implement one of those ways.  Customers expressing outrage, as proposed by the originator of this post, is necessary for them to see the need and act on it, though as we've all seen on other issues it may eventually take a change in management at the company to motivate a fix.<br>
<br>
My own opinion as to how it should be fixed?  Create a side quest which is a major timesink involving very rare drops off of common mobs in several different 50+ zones.  The end result of the side quest is an item that when turned in to a 12-hour spawning mob results in Ragefire appearing, and the item returned.  Remove non-epic loot from spawned Ragefire.  When the heart case is looted, both the pearl and the turn-in item must be combined in it to get the heart.  The timesink removes the dependence on the quest for an especially rare contended after spawn, yet maintains the low rate at which cleric epics enter the game.<br>
<br>
 - Chronomis<br>
