<br>
Well, here's a lesson I learned from my Mom.  If you don't get results, move up the food chain quickly =)<br>
<br>
These petitions regarding poor customer service (i.e. GMs who won't enforce the rules) should be sent to SONY, i.e. one of the big shots, CEO, chairman, etc.  Sending it to Verant does nothing, cause it all stays in house.  If the big whigs start getting annoyed a lot about poor CS at one of their subsidiaries, maybe something will happen.<br>
<br>
Monday, RF popped in SF.  One of our guildies had been camping there for a long time.  When it popped, he sent out the word, and we assembled.  As one of our druids was pulling it to us, it was stolen by another guild, and they took him out.  We petitioned immediately, and there was &gt;1&lt; GM online.  5 minutes later, after no response, the GM logged, and we heard nothing for the rest of the night.<br>
<br>
Notice, I'm not talking about whether Verant's rules are good (no KSing, what defines KSing, PnP, etc.) or not, but the fact that you can't get their own staff to enforce them.<br>
<br>
If it's a staffing issue, I'm sure they could afford to add some more GMs, at $13.00 x 400,000 x 12  per year (more for legends, plus fees to switch accounts, etc).<br>
<br>
